(:summary    "Major mode for editing PHP code"
 :repository (svn . "https://php-mode.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/php-mode")
 :created    "19990517"
 :updated    "20081212"
 :license    "GPL-3"
 :maintainer ("Aaron S. Hawley" . "ashawley@users.sourceforge.net")
 :provided   (php-mode)
 :required   ((("add-log" add-log)
	       ("cc-mode" cc-langs cc-mode)
	       ("emacs" custom font-lock)
	       ("etags" etags)
	       ("regexp-opt" regexp-opt)
	       ("speedbar" speedbar)))
 :keywords   (languages oop php)
 :wikipage   "http://www.emacswiki.org/PhpMode"
 :commentary "\
PHP mode is a major mode for editing PHP 3 and 4 source code.  It's
an extension of C mode; thus it inherits all C mode's navigation
functionality.  But it colors according to the PHP grammar and indents
according to the PEAR coding guidelines.  It also includes a couple
handy IDE-type features such as documentation search and a source
and class browser.

